    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-12-21T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-12-21T03:00:00-05:00" n="389"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d389">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/12899: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-12-21T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 21, 1934—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 21—1:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>591. Reference Legation’s 587, December 19, 5 p.m.<note n="92" xml:id="d389fn92"
                        >Not printed.</note> Atcheson telegraphed Peck at Nanking December 20th from
                    Wuhu that Olsons and Jacobsons have proceeded to Hankow and that all Americans
                    are now evacuated from southern Anhwei except those at Wuhu. He added that Wuhu
                    was quiet. He telegraphed Peck on December 21, <pb facs="0575" n="485"
                        xml:id="pg_485"/> 2 p.m., that he could not say Wuhu was adequately guarded
                    by Chinese unless more troops are stationed there nor that emergency was over
                    until Communists are definitely checked or diverted to some distance.</p>
                <p>One American, one British and one Japanese gunboat now at Wuhu.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
